OL,3,C'Die Hard is not a Christmas movie,'
OL,4,Crule British public in new survey
OL,6,FMore than half of respondents said
OL,7,Fthey check the age rating when
OL,8,Fselecting a film to watch as a family
OL,9,Fduring the holidays, which the BBFC
OL,10,Fsaid showed that responsible, age-
OL,11,Fappropriate viewing remains a key part
OL,12,Fof festive film nights.
OL,14,FDavid Austin, chief executive of the
OL,15,FBBFC, said: "With Home Alone crowned
OL,16,Fthe UK's favourite Christmas film, our
OL,17,Flatest research reveals that heart-
OL,18,Fwarming, family-friendly stories
OL,19,Fcontinue to sit at the heart of the
OL,20,Fnation's Christmas viewing traditions.
